ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The area in the United States comprised of a 68 square mile area northeast of the Potomac River donated by the state of Maryland.  The District of Columbia, also known as D.C., is not a state, nor is it part of any state.  It is a "federal district" established by the US Constitution as the seat of government. The district is occupied entirely by the city of Washington.

Concepts.definition: The area in the United States comprised of a 68 square mile area northeast of the Potomac River donated by the state of Maryland.  The District of Columbia, also known as D.C., is not a state, nor is it part of any state.  It is a "federal district" established by the US Constitution as the seat of government. The district is occupied entirely by the city of Washington.
